    • Method Detail

      • setRequestHandler

        void setRequestHandler(UiManager.RequestHandler handler)
        Sets the UiManager.RequestHandler. It is called when GitkitClient is initialized. The UiManager should call the corresponding handler method in UiManager.RequestHandler once the user has finished the interaction with the UI.
        Parameters:
        handler - the handler that handles requests from UiManager.
        See Also:
        UiManager.RequestHandler

      • showStartSignIn

        void showStartSignIn(GitkitUser.UserProfile lastUserProfile)
        Shows the initial sign in screen. It should show a proper UI to let the user choose/type in which account and/or identity provider he/she wants to use to sign in. Once such information is provided, UiManager.RequestHandler.handle(UiManager.Request) should be called with a UiManager.StartSignInRequest to proceed the flow.
        Parameters:
        lastUserProfile - the last used user profile.
        See Also:
        UiManager.RequestHandler.handle(UiManager.Request), UiManager.StartSignInRequest

      • showPasswordSignIn

        void showPasswordSignIn(java.lang.String email)
        Shows the password sign in screen. It should show a proper UI to let the user type in his/her password for the account specified by email. Once the password is provided and, UiManager.RequestHandler.handle(UiManager.Request) should be called with a UiManager.SignInWithPasswordRequest to proceed the flow.
        Parameters:
        email - the email address the user has chosen.
        See Also:
        UiManager.RequestHandler.handle(UiManager.Request), UiManager.SignInWithPasswordRequest

      • showPasswordSignUp

        void showPasswordSignUp(java.lang.String email)
        Shows the create password account screen. It should show a proper UI to let the user provide the password and display name to create a new account. Once such information is provided, UiManager.RequestHandler.handle(UiManager.Request) should be called with a UiManager.SignUpWithPasswordRequest to proceed the flow.
        Parameters:
        email - the email address the user has chosen to use.
        See Also:
        UiManager.RequestHandler.handle(UiManager.Request), UiManager.SignUpWithPasswordRequest

      • showPasswordAccountLinking

        void showPasswordAccountLinking(java.lang.String email,
                              IdProvider currentIdProvider)
        Shows the password account linking screen. If the user used to use password to sign in the account specified by email and now tries to sign in with an identity provider, he/she needs to be prompted to type in the password to verify he/she owns the account. Once the password is provided, UiManager.RequestHandler.handle(UiManager.Request) should be called with a UiManager.VerifyAccountWithPasswordRequest to proceed the flow.
        Parameters:
        email - the email address of the account the user tries to sign in.
        currentIdProvider - current identity provider the user signs in with.
        See Also:
        UiManager.RequestHandler.handle(UiManager.Request), UiManager.VerifyAccountWithPasswordRequest

      • showIdpAccountLinking

        void showIdpAccountLinking(java.lang.String email,
                         IdProvider previousIdProvider,
                         IdProvider currentIdProvider)
        Shows the identity provider account linking screen. If the user used to sign in with previousIdProvider and now tries to sign in with currentIdProvider, he/she needs to be prompted to confirm the attempt. Once the user confirms, UiManager.RequestHandler.handle(UiManager.Request) should be called with a UiManager.VerifyAccountWithIdpRequest such that a sign in with the previous identity provider flow is launched to verify the account ownership.
        Parameters:
        email - the email address of the account the user tries to sign in.
        previousIdProvider - the previous identity provider the user used to sign in with.
        currentIdProvider - the current identity provider the user signs in with.
        See Also:
        UiManager.RequestHandler.handle(UiManager.Request), UiManager.VerifyAccountWithIdpRequest

      • handleError

        void handleError(UiManager.ErrorCode code)
        Handles a user recoverable error. For example, if UiManager.ErrorCode.INVALID_PASSWORD happens, the password sign in screen should indicate the password is incorrect and let the user type in again.
        Parameters:
        code - the code of the error.
        See Also:
        UiManager.ErrorCode

      • dismiss

        void dismiss()
        Removes all the UI screens managed by this UiManager.
